{"type":"message","id":"cd1e24ce","parentId":"9f835be2","timestamp":"2026-02-11T19:27:32.334Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing Docker Configurations**\n\nI've identified three `docker-compose` files: `docker-compose.yml`, `docker-compose.prod.yml`, and `docker-compose.monitoring.yml`. My initial assessment suggests that `docker-compose.yml` serves as the primary configuration file, possibly integrating the other two. I plan to begin by thoroughly examining its contents to understand the core setup.\n\n\n**Understanding Dependency Structure**\n\nI've just finished the initial review of `docker-compose.yml`. I'm starting to grasp its basic setup, and I've noted a few key services. Next, I will delve into the `.prod` and `.monitoring` files, searching for deviations and added configurations that will shape the complete deployment architecture.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"Отлично, я вижу три файла `docker-compose`: `docker-compose.yml`, `docker-compose.prod.yml` и `docker-compose.monitoring.yml`.\n\nНачну с `docker-compose.yml`, чтобы понять основу. Затем я изучу `prod` и `monitoring` файлы, чтобы составить полную картину вашей Docker-конфигурации. Читаю `docker-compose.yml`.","textSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1770838052315_31","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docker-compose.yml"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-2.5-pro","usage":{"input":8239,"output":198,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8437,"cost":{"input":0.01029875,"output":0.00198,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012278750000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1770838044971}}
